Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.68,0:00:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as modern-day\Ncrimes involve people,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.65,0:00:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there are no\Nunsolvable mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.52,0:00:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's case is a train trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.32,0:00:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Schedules are\Nthe basis of judgment!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.41,0:00:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the\Nsingle truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.16,0:00:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.54,0:00:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.13,0:01:57.09,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Train Trick Murder Case
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.96,0:01:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Train Trick Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.09,0:02:00.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Yu-no-Yama (Mountain Hot Spring Town)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.39,0:02:04.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Yu-no-Yama Station
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.06,0:02:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.02,0:02:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where're we going?\NAren't we getting on this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.81,0:02:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, this is the Hana-no-Machi Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.52,0:02:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're riding the one up\Nthere, the Yu-no-Yama Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.49,0:02:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter which one we take--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.28,0:02:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,both lines connect\Nto a Tokyo-bound line
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.37,0:02:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at Hana-no-Machi\NStation anyways...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.28,0:02:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll miss the train\Nif we don't hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.04,0:02:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My head's pounding\Nfrom this hangover...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.08,0:02:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't shout so loud...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.92,0:02:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh. I don't feel up to this...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.89,0:02:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.31,0:02:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The food, the inn, and\Nthe hot spring were all great!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.44,0:02:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.78,0:02:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.44,0:02:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.74,0:03:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of your clients invited you on this trip
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.49,0:03:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as a reward for\Nsolving their case!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.12,0:03:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.46,0:03:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I'm the one\Nwho solved the case, not him...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.67,0:03:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna sleep for an hour\Nuntil we get to Hana-no-Machi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.21,0:03:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.22,0:03:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's your problem, Sato?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.38,0:03:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?\NYou don't need to get so mad...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.10,0:03:28.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You disgust me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.56,0:03:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't bear to sit\Nwith you any more!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.89,0:03:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to a different car!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.56,0:03:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Date!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.57,0:03:39.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't they--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.23,0:03:42.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, they stayed at the\Nsame inn as us last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.87,0:03:47.95,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kan'etsu Medical Association
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.17,0:03:54.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.29,0:03:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that group of doctors...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.96,0:03:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.76,0:04:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're from last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.93,0:04:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.84,0:04:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he's just upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.97,0:04:09.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are the other doctors?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.72,0:04:11.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We all left separately.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.31,0:04:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some took the Hana-no-Machi Line
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.14,0:04:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while others took the\NYu-no-Yama Line like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.48,0:04:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both lines end at\NHana-no-Machi Station anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.02,0:04:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then. Nighty-night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.37,0:04:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mizu-no-Kawa! Mizu-no-Kawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.21,0:04:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Mizu-no-Kawa Station?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.84,0:04:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it says we can transfer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.47,0:04:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we should transfer\Nto the Hana-no-Machi Line here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.14,0:04:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bzzt! Too bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.35,0:04:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Hana-no-Machi train\Narrived here at exactly 10:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.52,0:04:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was five minutes ago.\NIt's long gone by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.94,0:04:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.53,0:05:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to disturb you.\NTickets, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.00,0:05:15.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.50,0:05:17.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.25,0:05:22.80,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Mizu-no-Kawa Station
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.80,0:05:27.63,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Yu-no-Yama Line\NHana-no-Machi Line
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.26,0:05:29.80,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hana-no-Machi Station
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.10,0:05:33.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for using\Nthe Yu-no-Yama Line today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.77,0:05:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is our last stop,\NHana-no-Machi Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.77,0:05:40.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please look around once more to\Navoid forgetting anything onboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.73,0:05:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Passengers transferring\Nto the Tokyo-bound train
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.27,0:05:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will need to switch to Platform 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.94,0:05:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The next train will leave at 11:40.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.12,0:05:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thirty-five minutes of waiting...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.24,0:05:55.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Sato-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.79,0:05:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.12,0:06:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I calmed down after looking at\Nthe scenery from the very last car.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.42,0:06:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you might!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.88,0:06:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry 'bout that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.76,0:06:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like they made up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.39,0:06:10.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.76,0:06:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.35,0:06:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.39,0:06:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.31,0:06:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sure has a lot of change...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.82,0:06:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it was nice to meet you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.53,0:06:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Likewise!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.66,0:06:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mister! Your button's\Nabout to come off!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.74,0:06:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.50,0:06:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wiped it! How odd...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.75,0:06:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where was the body found?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.21,0:06:49.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside the Hana-no-Machi\Ntrain that arrived five minutes ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.63,0:06:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The victim appears to be a doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.26,0:06:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if it's a\Ndoctor from our group?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.64,0:06:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone did leave by themselves--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.56,0:06:59.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,one of them could have been\Non the Hana-no-Machi Line!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.81,0:07:00.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's check it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.56,0:07:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.23,0:07:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.36,0:07:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! What about your hangover?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.24,0:07:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's long gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.15,0:07:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stay silent after\Nhearing there's a dead body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.70,0:07:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Kogoro Mori's\Nexcitement has been piqued!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.92,0:07:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Utsumi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.47,0:07:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he was in your\Nmedical association?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.51,0:07:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Utsumi-{\i1}kun{\i0}.\NHe was with us last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.18,0:07:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that look?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.69,0:07:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Chief Railway Officer,\NYosuke Kobayashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.40,0:07:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an honor to meet you,\NDetective Mori!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.24,0:07:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your cooperation is\Ngreatly appreciated!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.20,0:07:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No problem. I'm glad to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.46,0:08:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what was the cause of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.83,0:08:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't know for\Nsure until the autopsy,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.92,0:08:09.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but my guess is cardiac arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.80,0:08:12.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, I'm of no use here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.97,0:08:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, isn't that a syringe mark?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.22,0:08:19.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You keep quiet! Wait, a syringe?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.39,0:08:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the vein on his arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.77,0:08:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a needle\Nmark with blood on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.10,0:08:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A mark from a hypodermic needle?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.61,0:08:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.44,0:08:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When intravenously given high\Ndoses of potassium chloride,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.53,0:08:37.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,people can die with\Nsymptoms just like cardiac arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.07,0:08:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.66,0:08:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hospitals have potassium\Nchloride and syringes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.41,0:08:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow. You sure know a lot, little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.00,0:08:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really like science stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.80,0:08:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was close!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.76,0:08:55.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't see\Nany syringes anywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.59,0:08:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.55,0:08:59.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was neither\Nan accident nor a suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.68,0:09:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a homicide! A murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.18,0:09:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.43,0:09:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in the way! Go outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.73,0:09:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.31,0:09:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then. The question is motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.40,0:09:10.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a simple robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.65,0:09:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's not a\Nsingle yen left in his wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.61,0:09:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And why are his fingers broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.03,0:09:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer was macho!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.28,0:09:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer held him down\Nso hard that it broke his fingers,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.41,0:09:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,prevented him from fighting back,\Nand then committed the crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.04,0:09:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would they really go through\Nthe trouble of giving him a shot
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.04,0:09:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just for that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.09,0:09:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Hana-no-Machi line runs\Nparallel to the Yu-no-Yama line,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.88,0:09:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which we took.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.42,0:09:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Yu-no-Yama\Nand Mizu-no-Kawa stations
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.05,0:09:39.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are the only places they meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.05,0:09:41.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The train this happened on
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.14,0:09:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,stopped at Mizu-no-Kawa\NStation at 10:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.31,0:09:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The question is\Nthe time of the murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.56,0:09:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the victim bought the\Ncanned coffee at around 10:50?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.61,0:09:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.73,0:09:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We had almost arrived\Nat Hana-no-Machi,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.11,0:09:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he was my last customer...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.82,0:10:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have any 1000-yen\Nbills to give him change with,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.99,0:10:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I gave him his change in coins,\Nwhich is why I remember him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.91,0:10:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was he sitting\Nby himself at the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.21,0:10:11.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.04,0:10:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And immediately afterward,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.34,0:10:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a mustached-man in a dark blue\Njacket and sunglasses sat next to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.88,0:10:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so you got up and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.35,0:10:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.89,0:10:24.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dark blue jacket?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.56,0:10:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the crime took place between\N10:50 and 10:52 or 10:53.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.40,0:10:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Dr. Date's\Njacket is reversible!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.53,0:10:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other side is dark blue!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.74,0:10:41.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe his button\Nwas about to come off
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.70,0:10:43.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because the victim had grabbed it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.20,0:10:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He broke his fingers\Ntrying to remove it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.08,0:10:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why he--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.75,0:10:50.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.96,0:10:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wiped the front of the button
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.96,0:10:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to remove the victim's fingerprints!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.63,0:10:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the victim died from an\Ninjection of potassium chloride,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.30,0:11:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which would be difficult\Nfor anyone but a doctor to get!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.22,0:11:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus his reaction when\Nhe heard the old man's name!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.97,0:11:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Date's probably the one responsible!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.81,0:11:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how could he have killed\Nsomeone on a different train?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.24,0:11:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, aren't you\Ngoing to do your job?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.90,0:11:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.20,0:11:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They've got a search\Nout for the robber.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.91,0:11:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My job here is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.87,0:11:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But was this really a robbery?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.29,0:11:31.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.96,0:11:37.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That witness lady seems\Na lot richer than the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.92,0:11:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And she was sitting nearby, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.09,0:11:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would the killer go after\Nthe man instead of the woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.14,0:11:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good question...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.06,0:11:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.10,0:11:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, why do you suppose\Nthat guy's sweating so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.94,0:11:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Sato.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.86,0:11:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't happen to\Nknow something, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.82,0:12:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? No, not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.99,0:12:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind.\NTell him, Sato-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.66,0:12:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell him that I had a big argument\Nwith Utsumi at the inn yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.04,0:12:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An argument? With the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.54,0:12:16.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.54,0:12:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It was a big one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.34,0:12:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What caused it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.80,0:12:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An unfounded accusation...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.51,0:12:27.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that I was receiving kickbacks\Nfrom a pharmaceutical company.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.97,0:12:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I'm completely innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.98,0:12:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, man. You don't seriously\Nthink I killed him, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.90,0:12:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing of the sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.94,0:12:40.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's clear that you and the\Nvictim were on different trains
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.15,0:12:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from what Mori-{\i1}san\N{\i0}and the others have said.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.11,0:12:47.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Dr. Date does have an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.37,0:12:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, why did you\Ntake the Yu-no-Yama Line
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.87,0:12:54.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,instead of the Hana-no-Machi Line?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.87,0:12:57.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could have ridden either one,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.50,0:12:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but Dr. Date bought me the ticket, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.25,0:13:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what was\Nthat argument earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.51,0:13:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to pay\Nhim back for my ticket,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.05,0:13:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he refused to accept my money.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.93,0:13:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He suddenly got angry\Nwhen I insisted he take it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.77,0:13:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know what to\Nthink when he blew up like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.06,0:13:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Dr. Date suggested\Ntaking the Yu-no-Yama Line
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.48,0:13:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then faked an argument\Nto move to the rear car...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.44,0:13:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ran.\NCan I see the train schedule?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.70,0:13:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The train schedule? Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.57,0:13:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.24,0:13:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.66,0:13:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he had transferred\Nto the Hana-no-Machi Line...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.37,0:13:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Mizu-no-Kawa Station\Nwould be the only place to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.79,0:13:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the Hana-no-Machi\Ntrain the victim was on
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.59,0:13:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,arrived at Mizu-no-Kawa\NStation at 10:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.93,0:13:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our Yu-no-Yama train\Narrived five minutes later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.77,0:13:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Hana-no-Machi train\Nwas long gone by then!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.23,0:13:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he couldn't\Nhave done it after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.52,0:13:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second! Didn't it say--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.56,0:14:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Yu-no-Yama Line is Line 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.44,0:14:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Hana-no-Machi Line is Line 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.90,0:14:09.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An overpass connects\NPlatforms 3 and 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.41,0:14:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The stairs are right\Nnext to the rear car,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.74,0:14:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which Dr. Date had all to himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.83,0:14:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Sounds like I'll\Nbe held up a little bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.96,0:14:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you close\Nthe office up for today?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.05,0:14:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.55,0:14:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.59,0:14:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A cell phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.97,0:14:33.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! I left Sonoko's\Npresent on the train!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.10,0:14:35.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.52,0:14:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I understand the trick\NDr. Date used to switch trains!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.28,0:14:49.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.15,0:14:51.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you forgot something,\Nthen ask Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.16,0:14:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! It's the killer\NI want you to find!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.33,0:15:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Is it my hangover?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.13,0:15:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.05,0:15:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Kogoro Mori.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.01,0:15:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would those involved please\Nassemble in the staff room?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.14,0:15:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.85,0:15:20.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've identified the real person\Nresponsible for this incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.81,0:15:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Date and Dr. Sato.\NPlease come as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.94,0:15:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The real person responsible?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.48,0:15:28.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't a robbery?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.78,0:15:34.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're busy, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.20,0:15:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this all about, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.37,0:15:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, the truth will become\Nclear in only fifteen minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.50,0:15:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying you'll point out\Nthe killer and have him arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.46,0:15:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in those fifteen minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.00,0:15:48.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, I am, Dr. Date.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.26,0:15:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you're going\Nto try to arrest me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.55,0:15:56.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The real person\Nresponsible for this incident
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.01,0:15:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is you, Dr. Date!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.52,0:15:59.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.68,0:16:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.81,0:16:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.23,0:16:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was on the same\NYu-no-Yama train as us!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.65,0:16:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can only confirm that for the first\Nfive minutes after the train departed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.11,0:16:13.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't see him again until we\Narrived at Hana-no-Machi Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.49,0:16:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.41,0:16:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he transfer?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.83,0:16:20.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. At Mizu-no-Kawa Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.29,0:16:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At Mizu-no-Kawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.16,0:16:24.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't that impossible, time-wise?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.38,0:16:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a good look.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.96,0:16:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Yu-no-Yama train arrived on\NPlatform 1 of Mizu-no-Kawa Station
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.34,0:16:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at 10:35.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.89,0:16:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Long after the Hana-no-Machi\Ntrain on Platform 6 had left!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.39,0:16:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could I have\Npossibly transferred trains?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.43,0:16:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A single phone call\Nwould make it possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.86,0:16:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A phone call?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.44,0:16:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you call from a cell\Nphone one train stop ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.82,0:16:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and ask them to hold\Nthe Hana-no-Machi train
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.74,0:16:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because you left something on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.37,0:17:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,10:35.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.16,0:17:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before you arrived\Nat Mizu-no-Kawa Station,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.42,0:17:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you turned your\Nreversible jacket inside-out
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.96,0:17:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and disguised yourself with\Na fake mustache and other props.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.09,0:17:14.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you arrived at the station,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.05,0:17:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you ran up the overpass
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.84,0:17:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and headed for\NLine 6 as fast as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.39,0:17:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you started\Nan argument with Dr. Sato
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.77,0:17:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and moved to the last car\Nimmediately after the train departed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.06,0:17:28.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had the train employees\Nsearch for a missing item
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.44,0:17:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to delay the Hana-no-Machi\Ntrain's departure,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.61,0:17:33.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,allowing you to\Nget on in the nick of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.28,0:17:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had probably\Ninstructed the victim to sit there
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.95,0:17:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,before you killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.70,0:17:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.08,0:17:46.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}'s right; there was\Nboth a phone call and a search.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.54,0:17:48.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man was distressed because\Nhe had forgotten a contract
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.79,0:17:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,more important than his life,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.00,0:17:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it never turned up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.92,0:17:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow. But how exactly is that proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.47,0:18:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was the call recorded and\Nvoice-matched with my voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.76,0:18:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.10,0:18:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was on the Yu-no-Yama\Ntrain the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.06,0:18:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then please show us your ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.10,0:18:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ticket inspection took place on\Nthe Yu-no-Yama train at around 10:40.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.40,0:18:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you didn't transfer,\Nthen it should have a stamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.07,0:18:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we see your ticket, Date-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.33,0:18:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I lost it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.24,0:18:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You lost it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.29,0:18:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to do a body search?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.00,0:18:32.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, there's no proof\NI was on the train the entire time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.50,0:18:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's no proof\NI transferred, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.09,0:18:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Innocent before proven guilty."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.13,0:18:39.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.18,0:18:44.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I can't waste\Nany more time here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.43,0:18:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.93,0:18:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which platform for\Nthe train to Tokyo, again?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.10,0:18:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.15,0:18:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Date.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.45,0:19:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there still something left?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.66,0:19:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You certainly had a\Nlot of change in your wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.37,0:19:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.71,0:19:14.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's entirely possible that\Nthe killer took the victim's money
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.34,0:19:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from his wallet--\Nincluding all of his change--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.88,0:19:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make it look like a robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.18,0:19:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's your point?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.47,0:19:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.27,0:19:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but Utsumi-{\i1}kun\N{\i0}was with me last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.52,0:19:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We both chipped\Nin to buy cigarettes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.06,0:19:38.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so it wouldn't be that\Nodd to find his fingerprints
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.61,0:19:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on the money inside my wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.90,0:19:43.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.74,0:19:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.12,0:19:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not referring to\Nthe victim's fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.79,0:19:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.04,0:19:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?\NWhose fingerprints would there be?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.21,0:19:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.09,0:19:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right before he was murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.76,0:20:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the victim bought canned\Ncoffee from the onboard vendor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.93,0:20:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was the last customer,\Nand he pulled out a 10,000-yen bill,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.39,0:20:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so the vendor remembers him!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.27,0:20:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. That train\Nvendor's fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.32,0:20:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Date.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.20,0:20:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fingerprints of the vendor\Non the Hana-no-Machi train,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.91,0:20:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which you supposedly weren't on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.41,0:20:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they happen to be on\Nany of the coins in your wallet...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.52,0:20:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the rumor really was true?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.69,0:20:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.27,0:21:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was receiving kickbacks!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.03,0:21:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then he caught me and\Ntried to blackmail me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.45,0:21:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He demanded money.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.33,0:21:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said if I didn't pay up,\Nit would become more than a rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.12,0:21:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He threatened to send\Nincriminating photographs
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.00,0:21:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to my medical association\Nand the hospital I work at!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.92,0:21:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when I decided to\Nagree to a deal to get the film
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.46,0:21:22.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and kill him on the train!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.63,0:21:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found it hard to believe he\Nwould hand over all the negatives!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.97,0:21:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.80,0:21:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someday the rumor would\Nbecome the target of investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.89,0:21:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So instead, you planned to\Nuse an alibi trick involving trains
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.15,0:21:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to avoid suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.02,0:21:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the perfect plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.48,0:21:43.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like all of my big operations!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.65,0:21:47.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even the most skilled\Nphysicians are human.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.07,0:21:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunate as it may be,\Neven they make bad diagnoses!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.74,0:21:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People are imperfect-- no crime\Nthey commit will ever be flawless!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.72,0:23:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a nice nap...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.30,0:23:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hana-no-Machi?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.18,0:23:37.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are we still here, again?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.39,0:23:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since we're already here,\Nlet's stay another night at a hot spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.06,0:23:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hana-no-Machi Hot Spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.15,0:23:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another night?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.23,0:23:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds great! Let's do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.15,0:23:49.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.15,0:23:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But another night\Ndoes sound like fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.74,0:23:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurray!
